article.description: LaToya Thomas scored 18 points to lead the host Cleveland Rockers to a 79-74 victory over the Washington Mystics on Friday night. Chamique Holdsclaw led Washington with 27 points and 12 rebounds.
article.headline: Rookie Thomas leads Cleveland over Washington
article.linkText: Even healthy Holdsclaw not enough vs. Rockers
article.story:
CLEVELAND (AP) -- LaToya Thomas scored 18 points to lead the Cleveland Rockers to a 79-74 victory over the Washington Mystics on Friday night.

Chamique Holdsclaw had 27 points and 12 rebounds to lead Washington (2-7), which overcame a 19-point deficit but lost its fourth straight and seventh in eight games.

Thomas, a rookie, shot 7-for-11 from the field and matched her high in points. She also scored 18 against Connecticut on Wednesday night. The forward from Mississippi State -- the first pick in the WNBA draft -- had 11 points in the second half as Cleveland held off Washington.

Holdsclaw scored 10 points early in the second half to spark the Mystics in her second game back since missing four because of a strained hamstring.

A 3-pointer by the Mystics' Stacey Dales-Schuman tied it at 61 with 9:19 left. Washington's Nakia Sanford was fouled away from the ball on the play and made the free throw to put the Mystics ahead.

Thomas made two free throws with 8:47 left to put Cleveland ahead 63-62. Minutes later, she stole a cross-court pass and fed Betty Lennox for a layup that made it 71-65.

Lennox finished with 17 points and center Chasity Melvin had 12 points and 12 rebounds for Cleveland (5-3), which is 4-1 at home.

Murriel Page and Coco Miller scored nine points for the Mystics.

Lennox and Thomas scored eight points apiece in the first half as the Rockers took a 43-33 halftime lead. Cleveland's reserves outscored the Washington bench 26-6 in the first half.

Cleveland used a 17-2 run to open a 35-16 lead.

Holdsclaw had 11 points in the first half despite shooting just 3-for-13. She made all five of her free throws in the first half and finished 9-for-9 from the line.
